        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 3:24PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northeast of Union, or near Lockhart. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lockhart, Sharon, Adamsburg, Saratt, and Bullock Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
